{"@context":"http://schema.org/","@type":"CreativeWork","@id":"https://d.lib.ncsu.edu/collections/catalog/0006782","url":"https://d.lib.ncsu.edu/collections/catalog/0006782","name":"Dean David Chaney, Dr. Charles Goldthwait, and former governor Luther Hodges","description":"Dr. David Chaney (left), Dean of the College of Textiles, with Dr. Charles Goldthwait (center), and former governor Luther Hodges (right). Dr. Chaney is handing Dr. Goldthwait a dollar bill, his annual salary for conducting research at the University. Transcribed from accompanying material: NCSU Octogenarian Gets \"Salary\": \"Pay up!\" dollar-a-year man Luther Hodges (right) commands as Dr. David Chaney (on the left), dean of the North Carolina State University School of Textiles, complies by handing a dollar bill to Dr. Charles Goldthwait, who still conducts research at the age of 52 although he retired from the payroll years ago. Former Governor Hodges retired from the business world of textiles to the political world, then retired from government to his present dollar-a-year job as Chairman of the Board for the Research Triangle Foundation.","thumbnailUrl":"https://iiif.lib.ncsu.edu/iiif/0006782/full/350,/0/default.jpg","image":"https://iiif.lib.ncsu.edu/iiif/0006782/full/350,/0/default.jpg","dateCreated":"1960","about":[{"@type":"Thing","name":"Governors"},{"@type":"Thing","name":"College administrators"},{"@type":"Thing","name":"People"},{"name":"Hodges, Luther Hartwell, 1898-1974","@type":"Person","familyName":"Hodges","givenName":"Luther Hartwell","birthDate":"1898","deathDate":"1974","gender":"male"},{"name":"Goldthwait, Charles F.","description":"Charles F. Goldthwait graduated from Worcester (Mass.) Polytechnic Institute with a B.S. in Chemistry.  After 50 years of service in textile research he joined the faculty of NC State College in 1956 as a Visiting Professor of Textile Chemistry.  He was the originator of the semi-elastic cotton gauze bandage and the differential dye test for maturity and processing quality of cotton.  He received an honorary degree from NCSU in 1965.  Goldwaith received the Olney Medal for outstanding achievement in textile chemistry.","@type":"Person","familyName":"Goldthwait","givenName":"Charles F.","birthDate":"1886","gender":"male"},{"name":"Chaney, David Webb, 1915-2004","description":"Dr. David Chaney was Dean of the NCSU School of Textiles from 1967 to 1981.","@type":"Person","familyName":"Chaney","givenName":"David Webb","birthDate":"1915","deathDate":"2004","gender":"male"},{"name":"North Carolina State University -- Administration","@type":"Organization"}],"keywords":["Governors","College administrators","People"],"genre":["Group portraits","Photographs","Publicity photographs"],"inLanguage":["eng"],"isPartOf":["https://d.lib.ncsu.edu/collections/catalog?f%5Bispartof_facet%5D%5B%5D=University+Archives+Photographs"]}